<title>SRI LANKA: Sri Lanka T-bill yields continue to slide.</title>
<headline>Sri Lanka T-bill yields continue to slide.</headline>
<dateline>COLOMBO 1997-01-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Sri Lankan treasury bill yields continued their downward slide on Wednesday, the first auction of 1997.</p>
<p>A central bank release said the weighted average of three, six and 12-month bills fell by 0.31 percentge points, 0.37 percentage points and 0.27 percentage points.</p>
<p>			bids received   bids accepted   avg yield</p>
<p>     3 months     3,854	     1,801	  17.14 (17.45)</p>
<p>     6 months	 815		 375	  17.03 (17.40)</p>
<p>    12 months     5,463	     3,136	  17.11 (17.38)</p>
<p>NOTE - Bids in million rupees, yields in percent (previous week's yields in brackets).</p>
<p>--Colombo newsroom (941) 434319</p>
